  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Chronic Obstructive Pulmonary Disease (COPD) patients are more likely to develop acute
      hypercapnic respiratory failure. In the acute phase, non invasive ventilation has been shown
      to improve mortality and reduce intubation rate. Few studies are available about long term
      benefits of home non invasive ventilation in COPD patients with chronic hypercapnic
      respiratory failure who survived after an acute episode. The purpose of this study is to
      determine whether home non invasive ventilation can reduce recurrent acute hypercapnic
      respiratory failure in COPD patients who survived an acute hypercapnic respiratory failure
      episode treated by non invasive ventilation.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
